 1+ 5 * 2^m =n^2
m\ge 2
5\cdot2^m=n^2-1
n\pm1
(n-1,n+1)=(n-1,n+1-(n-1))=(n+1,2)=2
d>0
n+1,n-1, d
n+1-(n-1)=2
\implies (n-1,n+1)|2\implies (n-1,n+1)=2
n\pm1
\left(\frac{n+1}2,\frac{n-1}2\right)=1
5\cdot2^{m-2}=\frac{n+1}2\cdot \frac{n-1}2
\displaystyle\frac{n+1}2=5; \frac{n-1}2=2^{m-2}
\displaystyle\frac{n-1}2=5; \frac{n+1}2=2^{m-2}
\displaystyle\frac{n-1}2=5\cdot2^{m-2} ;\frac{n+1}2=1
\displaystyle\frac{n+1}2=5\cdot2^{m-2} ;\frac{n-1}2=1
